README-git

$ git clone https://github.com/larsrh/libisabelle.git

$ git status
$ gitg –all &
$ git pull
$ git reset --hard  # Reset tracked files to match the most recent commit
$ git clean -f      # Remove untracked files
$ git commit -am "xxxxx"
$ git push

# https://help.github.com/articles/merging-an-upstream-repository-into-your-fork/
$ git pull https://github.com/larsrh/libisabelle.git
# this makes a merge, conflicts to be handled separately in editor.
# SEE http://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Git-Basics-Undoing-Things
#     http://www.gitguys.com/topics/merging-with-a-conflict-conflicts-and-resolutions
# but then there might be: 
#   U  file
#   gitg –all: Unstaged changes ...
$ git reset
$ git commit -am "xxxxx"

